JD - 4 :

##Key Responsibilities
- Design, implement, and optimize FPGA-based digital logic using Verilog / SystemVerilog / VHDL
- Lead FPGA development activities including architecture definition, RTL implementation, and timing closure
- Perform functional verification, simulation, and on-board validation of FPGA designs
- Work on system-level integration and debug of FPGA-based solutions
- Develop embedded firmware in C/C++ for FPGA-based systems and embedded processors
- Integrate and validate high-speed interfaces and industry-standard protocols
- Support FPGA synthesis, place & route, and constraint development
- Drive hardware bring-up and root-cause analysis using lab debug tools
- Develop automation and build scripts using TCL / Perl
- Collaborate with board, firmware, and system teams during integration and validation phases

##Required Skills & Experience
- 6–9 years of hands-on experience in FPGA design, verification, and hardware validation
- Strong background in digital logic design and RTL development
- Proficiency in Verilog / SystemVerilog / VHDL
- Experience with embedded firmware development using C/C++
- Hands-on experience with ARM-based embedded processors
- Working knowledge of high-speed and complex protocols, including:
  - PCIe Gen4 / Gen5
  - DDR
  - 10G Ethernet
  - USB 3.2
  - JESD204C
  - IEEE 1588 PTP
  - MIPI, MACSEC
- Strong system-level design and debug experience
- Hands-on experience with high-speed memory interfaces such as QDR II+ and QDR IV
- Proficiency in hardware debug using logic analyzers, ChipScope, and oscilloscopes
- Experience with scripting and automation using TCL / Perl

